{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608132","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608132"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:29:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:29:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15983"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15983","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15983"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.36,0,0.11,0.39,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8674"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73460"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8674","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8674"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15983"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58929"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7567"},{"type":"tags","id":"8606"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20763"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20768"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73460","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73460"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring early embryological development, the amnion develops as a protective membrane surrounding the developing embryo. This membrane has distinct tissue layers that form through specific developmental processes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the tissue that forms the outer layer of the amniotic membrane?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Epiblast","Exocoelomic cyst","Extra-embryonic coelom","Extraembryonic somatic mesoderm","Extraembryonic splanchnic mesoderm"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring early embryological development, the formation of protective membranes around the embryo is crucial. The amnion develops as a membrane that will eventually surround the embryo and contain amniotic fluid. The outer layer of the amnion is specifically formed by the \u003Cstrong\u003Eextraembryonic somatic mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eepiblast\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to the embryo proper and amniotic ectoderm but does not form the outer layer of the amnion. It is the source of all three germ layers of the embryo.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eexocoelomic cyst\u003C/strong\u003E is a transient structure that appears during early development but does not contribute to the formation of the amniotic membrane.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextra-embryonic coelom\u003C/strong\u003E is the fluid-filled space between the amnion and chorion, rather than a tissue layer itself. It forms when the extraembryonic mesoderm splits into somatic and splanchnic layers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eextraembryonic splanchnic mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E lines the yolk sac and forms part of the chorion, but does not contribute to the amnion\u0027s outer layer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these embryological structures is important as abnormalities in their development can lead to various pregnancy complications including amniotic band syndrome and chorioamniotic separation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Extraembryonic somatic mesoderm forms the outer layer of the amnion and chorion during early embryological development.","The extraembryonic mesoderm splits into somatic and splanchnic layers, creating the extraembryonic coelom.","Understanding the formation of extraembryonic membranes is crucial for comprehending early pregnancy development and complications."],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epub 2014 Mar 5. PMID: 24603318; PMCID: PMC4258770","Chen X, Liu H, Li Y, Zhang W, Zhou A, Xia W, Xu S. First-trimester fetal size, accelerated growth in utero, and child neurodevelopment in a cohort study. BMC Med. 2024 Apr 29;22(1):181. doi: 10.1186/s12916-024-03390-3. PMID: 38685041; PMCID: PMC11059611","Godfrey KM, Inskip HM, Hanson MA. The long-term effects of prenatal development on growth and metabolism. Semin Reprod Med. 2011 May;29(3):257-65. doi: 10.1055/s-0031-1275518. Epub 2011 Jul 18. PMID: 21769765; PMCID: PMC3685133","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58929"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15983"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58929"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T21:13:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T21:15:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8674"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73460"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":